==English==
=== Etymology ===
From {{Dan.}} ''[[isbjerg]]'' or {{Norw.}} ''[[isberg]]'' both meaning ''mountain of ice''. First used to describe a glacier as seen at a distance from a ship then used as a term to describe the floating chunks of ice broken off from such glaciers.

=== Noun ===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''iceberg''' ([[icebergs]])

#A huge mass of ocean-floating [[ice]] which has broken off a [[glacier]].
#:''The '''Titanic''' hit an iceberg and sank''.

